        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Ukraine to provide expertise on countering Shahed drones to Gulf countries Middle East Issued on: 06/03/2026 - 15:08 Various countries, including the United States have asked Ukraine for its expertise in countering Iran’s Shahed drones. Russia has fired tens of thousands of these drones at its neighbour since the war began just over four years ago. Ukraine's President Zelensky said they will provide assistance as long as it doesn't weaken his country' own defences. Israelis on border with Lebanon stay put despite Hezbollah strike threat 06/03/2026 Middle East In Israel, a unique network of volunteer first responders 06/03/2026 Middle East Hezbollah has \"less wriggle room\" as Lebanese \"lose their patience\" 06/03/2026 Middle East Displaced Lebanese speak of their experience amid Israeli airstrikes 06/03/2026 Middle East Middle East conflict threatens food security in Gulf countries 06/03/2026 Middle East Israeli airstrikes pound Lebanon, displacing hundreds of thousands 06/03/2026 Middle East US likely responsible for Iranian girls' school bombing, investigation says 06/03/2026 Middle East US Congress rejects 'war powers resolution' that would halt strikes in Iran 06/03/2026 Middle East Donald Trump seeks Kyiv's help in defending against Iranian drones 06/03/2026 Middle East"
